data.title: Gorgeous!
data.text: This Catholic church is stunningly beautiful! Over 100 years old with a storied history just as long, this church is worth a stop. Not sure if tours are given... I attend Mass there and have also been for several baptisms and weddings. If you do visit, please be mindful of any services that be going on. Otherwise, the history and decor make it a sight to see.

data.title: Just beautiful
data.text: If you're downtown Jacksonville definitely take a stop over just to see the architecture. It's a beautiful old building with spires and sculptures. It's a real beauty

data.title: Exquisite Architecture
data.text: This Catholic Basilica is well worth a visit for those interested in churches and architecture. Beautifully maintained. The basement gift shop is also worth a quick stop.
